'''Kifraya''', '''Kafraiya''',  ({{lang-ar|كفريا}})    is a [[village]]  in the [[Koura District]], in the [[Northern Governorate]] of [[Lebanon]]. The population is  [[Maronite Christianity in Lebanon|Maronite]] and [[Sunni Islam in Lebanon|Sunni]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Municipal and ikhtiyariah elections in Northern Lebanon |url=http://www.localiban.org/IMG/pdf/iiMonthly-Municip-Mar10-E92.pdf |publisher=The Monthly |accessdate=31 October 2016 |page=23 |date=March 2010 |deadurl=bot: unknown |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160603040803/http://www.localiban.org/IMG/pdf/iiMonthly-Municip-Mar10-E92.pdf |archivedate= 3 June 2016 |df= }}</ref>  The village is famous for the  Georges family.<ref>[http://www.kifraya.com/default.htm Kifraya website]</ref>

