'''Thuvaraiyam Pathi''' is described in [[Ayyavazhi mythology]]. The [[Akilattirattu Ammanai]], the holy text of [[Ayyavazhi]], tells about a sunken land at about 152 miles either south or south-east to [[Kanyakumari (town)|Kanyakumari]], with 16008 streets. 

This land also matches the sunken land, [[Kumarikkandam]] of ancient [[Tamil Nadu]].

